723589f-a.title: Manhattan: Union Square Park - The wooden battleship - [Union Square - 14th Street (East).]
723589f-a.text:
Union Square Parks ''The wooden battle ship that never went to Sec''
located in the southern end of the Park, at the head of Broadway. This
structure erected during the early days of the World War was used mainly
as an enlistment agency. Photographer's vantage point for this set of
three viewa is East 14th Street at Broadway and viewing northward.
1916.
Nicholas Savostayanoff.
